<br>
His eyes fell on a picture standing on the table in front of them.  He reached out and picked it up, looking at it closely.  &quot;Who is this?&quot; he asked her.<br>
<br>
He could sense her sadness as she reached over to gently touch the picture herself.  &quot;This is my Mother.  Her name is Tiriana Silverfang.&quot;<br>
<br>
The picture was of a lovely half-elf with dark hair.  From the clothing she wore she was clearly a Druid.  Kriyena had once closely resembled her mother, in her days when she herself had been a Druid.  Before she had become a Shamaness and transformed into the semblance of a Barbarian.<br>
<br>
Edonil looked down at her, and she could sense his concern.  He sat down beside her on the bench, pulling her to him.  With the bond they shared, he realized that something had happened to this woman.  &quot;Vhere is dosst Ilharn, d'anthe?&quot;<br>
<br>
Kriyena leaned against him, putting her arm around his waist.  Quietly, fighting back tears, she told him of Tiriana Silverfang.  Of the day she had come home from her day of training to find that her Mother had vanished without a trace.  She told him of how one of her comrades had informed her that he had seen Tiriana in Oggok, enslaved to an Ogre there.  She recalled the day the Lust for Blood had attacked Oggok in an attempt to help her find her Mother.  And tears finally fell down her cheeks as she told him that she still did not know for sure where her Mother was.  That she was lost to her.<br>
<br>
